Fellowship<br />
<br />
Use Eomer and Eowyn to pull Legolas out of the deck. This makes any tough minion pulled on you either dead or fighting a ten strength Eomer. Use Eowyn to prevent wounds to Eomer and when she is exausted sacrifice her to a tough minion. Move one site at a time, healing yourself and shooting your opponents down. Any tough minions get through use Sam as a sacrificial lamb and just throw Eomer and Aragorn against just about anything. Use Faramir exclusivly against Men if it is possible. Nazgul should be the only deck that should give you a problem and then only on till you get a Elrond with Vilya. Try to empty as much of your hand as possible to prepare for your Shadow phase each turn.<br />
<br />
Shadow<br />
<br />
This is a typical-not so typical deck but it is frightening when it gets going. I&#39;ve played as many as 14 goblins against an opponent. While it may seem otherwise this deck flies through cards. The key to victory is a given Swarm, Swarm and Swarm some more. Also a lot of you critics are thinking about my deck list and saying why a Balrog. The answer is the Suprise not many players are expecting to face a Balrog anymore. But with Power and Terror you could get a 2 twilight Balrog and then have a Balrog Swarm also from the new expansion coming out their is going to be a site 9 underground location with 9 twilight perfect Balrog territory.<br />
<br />
Anyway thanks for taking the time to read this strategy I am looking forward to hearing helpful comments.<br />
<br />
Yours Truly Zak Cardwell </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
